for everyone.  Here's the latest youtube thing I found an it is awesome.  It's called Animusic.  Here's my favorite but there are at least 15 of them.

I doubt any of you know because I haven't told you and have only now been able to acquire a computer for a short time.  Last Wednesday someone burglarized our apartment.  I have not labeled it as a certain race but rather someone who knows mac computers are worth a great deal in pawn shops or someone who needs drug money.  The break in was with a crowbar.  I was pretty angry up until Saturday evening.  I lost my computer and all sorts of files and downloads that were important to me, not to mention that my identity could be stolen.  So anyway I just thought I'd let everyone know that you aren't totally safe.  I kinda wish I could go back and not go into work so I could see who did it.  One of my roommates is very suspect.  On a brighter note I'm leaving tonight to come to Montevallo.  If you're free I'll see you guys tomorrrow.  peace.

The world is over.  Mainly because of this...the Spice Girls are reuniting.

http://breakingnews.iol.ie/entertainment/story.asp?j=223715162&p=zz37y5868

1. Movie reviews:  So I must say that I watched Apocalypto Friday and wasn't impressed.  Every animal was fake.  It was like stuffed animals attacking people.  It was an ok idea but needed more of an ending.  V for Vendetta which I finished last night at 3 am was awesome.  Mainly the fact that V withstood several bullets and then proceeded to kill every man with knives.  I wanted it to be real.  Then comes the best part of my day.  I finally watched Boondock Saints for the first time and I loved it.  I wanted that to be real as well.  So those are the three movies I watched in the last 72 hours.  IT doesn't hold a candle to what Brian and Joie did though.

2. Because Joie is so happy about tetris I figured I'd give this link on wikipedia (not confirming it's truth) that there are secrets and cheats you can use in the game.  The cheats are at the bottom.

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tetris_%28Game_Boy%29  

3. It appears that I will not be in Montevallo on the 12th but sometime between the 17th-22nd.  I'm starting to despise work.  

4. Stop reading this.

1.This has to be one of the funniest things I've found on the internet.  Thank you Japan.  Watch it all the way through because they put it in a real world scenario.  

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P1S9t8XFcOA

2. I'm stealing Joie's numbering system.

3. Today while I was washing clothes at the laudromat and talking to my mom on the phone I mentioned being a drummer.  I also mentioned how a friend of mine auditioned for the Blue Man Group and got rejected.(see #4)  A lady was also there and as I was leaving wanted to know if I knew anyone here that could teach her 4 year old drums.  I gave her my professor's card and also told her about Memphis drum shop.  She is originally from Memphis but spent the last 10 months in Alabaster.  She said she had called Montevallo for an instructor to teach her kid.  Of course the only one they have is you know who.  Evidently he didn't have time to do it.  Thus we spent 15 minutes talking about me transferring up here from the Montevallo.  Small world.

4. see #5

5.  Do not audition for the Blue Man Group unless you have acting experience.  Any drummer without it will not be considered.  They will however be considered for the band behind the Blue Man Group.  I can expand later but I've already blogged enough to last me the rest of the year.  

6.

7. bye.

My two favorite things combined...drums and video games.  Maybe not the best drummer but at least he is creative.  I have too much time on my hands.

http://youtube.com/watch?v=SZqwvjwqwK4

I'm somewhat bored.  I found this awesome satellite photo of the moon. 

moon.google.com

Zoom all the way in and the detail of it is incredible.  No it is not one of those turn your volume up and an alien jumps out at your face.  Plus you can see where the apollo missions landed.(if you believe we went there)  It's pretty cool. peace.

Check this out.  Heather you need to do this for your senior recital.(encore at least)

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=59ZX5qdIEB0&NR

peace.

get your stocking
 Since I don't feel like studying I copied Heather with this stocking thing. I also needed some Dream Theater. So I am watching the video of "Finally Free." The song is ok, it gets very good the last 3 minutes when Mike Portnoy(the drummer) goes crazy. It just sucks I have to let the full 11 minute song load. I made a C in conducting. No biggie. I'm also enjoying listening to John, better known as Caveman John or the guy who talks to himself have outbursts in the library lab. It's funnier to watch people stare at him. I'm going to be nice to everyone for the remainder of the week.(or at least try to) For all that I won't see this week have a great Christmas. peace.
Basic conducting final is going to suck hard.  I didn't know what to study so I didn't.  It was probably not a good idea, but I don't care about it.  Joie sucks as well.

Thanks to Heather for finding this pic for me.  Life stinks.  I wonder when I'll ever finish my paper for Music History seeing as how I don't she didn't give us our second draft back before the break.  I'll never finish it.  I'm also not looking forward to Thursday's concert.  It feels like a waste of time for me.  If I wanted to play middle school parts I'd drop out of college and retake eigth grade classes.  I also need to finish my composition project and practice conducting.

Thanksgiving was great.  I spent time with Karen's family doing the engaged thing.  It's not that great because now  her mom is set on planning the wedding for us without our consent.  It ticks me off.  Other than that it was fun.  I'm ready for Christmas break.

So I found out yesterday that I'm not the only one that feels the Music Department has screwed them over.  Some had major issues others had minor issues.  The bad thing is I'm bored.  I'm so bored I tend to stare at the wall rather than study for Music History.  Then there's the lack of having a decent paying job.  5.15 an hour just doesn't cut it.  That's about as much as I can rant simply because I'm tired.  peace

New cell phone, the number is 205-790-4953.  That's for anyone who cares are may call me in the near future.  You prank me you die!

So I finally have time to update. Mainly because I can get to a computer today.  I noticed a lot of people were confused on how Professor X could inhabit the man's body.  One of my roommates who practically read every comic said that when Professor X dies he became pure telekinetic energy and therefore could go where he pleased.  Thus he inhabited the man in the bed.  He also said that even though the movie killed Cyclops, The Phoenix, and several others they pretty much came back in the comics.  The movie was great though.  It gave me something to do after cutting grass from 7am-5pm.  Go see it.  I was glad they killed Cyclops fast. I'm still in Montevallo if anyone wants to hang out. peace.

So since everyone else is ticked off at something I'll join the club.  I did not pass my percussion barrier.  Why?  Jay Burnham.  Ok, so I didn't practice as much as needed, but I could have had an accompainist on my mallet piece.  I didn't find that out until two weeks ago.(after I'd been playing the same dam piece since January)  So it's all or nothing.  I'll retake my barrier in the fall, pass it and then find a way to take lessons from a good teacher.  Why does the Wind Ensemble not have percussionists or for that matter why there is no one who is a percussion major?  Jay Burnham.  Go figure.  No one wants to take from a man with his reputation.  The guys at Birmingham Percussion laughed when I uttered his name.  He deserves to get kicked in the balls. To quote a fellow music major, "How can you fail your barrier?  You're the principal player!"  That's right.  If I'm the principal player in the Wind Ensemble but can't pass my barrier there are some things wrong.  First, I either suck real bad and didn't practice.(failing was all my fault) Second, Tina should be principal player this semester.(since I couldn't pass my barrier that makes her the stronger player)  Third, because I'm one of two declared percussionists in the department they chose me because I am the stronger player.  Four, it's all legistics and the principal spot means nothing.  So either take my scholarship away or explain why I failed my barrier.  Something doesn't add up.  I'm done for today and probably for the next month or two.  Good luck to everyone else trying to pass their barrier.  peace

Ten Top Trivia Tips about Nick Lowery!

  1. On stone temples in southern India, there are more than 30 million carved images of Nick Lowery.
  2. Cats use their Nick Lowery to test whether a space is large enough for them to fit through.
  3. Nick Lowery was declared extinct in 1902!
  4. Nick Lowery is the smallest of Jupiter's many moons.
  5. Over 2000 people have now climbed Nick Lowery, with roughly ten percent dying on the way down.
  6. Only one person in two billion will live to be Nick Lowery.
  7. Nick Lowery never said 'Play it again, Sam'!
  8. Worldwide, Nick Lowery is the most important natural enemy of night-flying insects.
  9. The word 'samba' means 'to rub Nick Lowery'!
  10. In the kingdom of Bhutan, all citizens officially become Nick Lowery on New Year's Day.

Can you believe this mess. I never knew I was famous or extinct.

So last night I practiced with the Purple Side Orchestra.  I'm not really big into college night but last night made me want to play every year from now.  We sound great.  Once again Heather forced me to update.  She's right, I'm a gold at heart but that's only because my family all went here before me and they were all gold.  However, this year and maybe next year I'm purple.  So here's to the purple side.  I hope the gold side has better music if not well they are just screwed.  peace. PV

Well it's about time.  Congrats to Heather who got me to update this thing.  So what are five of life's simple pleasures I enjoy. 

1. silence. I normally don't find time to sit and listen to the stillness, mainly because it only occurs when everyone is asleep.(including me)

2. loyalty.  If you aren't loyal to me don't expect loyalty back.  Loyalty is the trait that pulls me to new people.

3. talent.  I take mine for granted.

4. friends.  I seem to believe that I have none, and when I sit and think about I come to find I have more than I deserve.

5. love.  I don't deserve it.

By the way no recital class tomorrow.
peace.

My update again will be rather boring.  I recently watched Batman the movie.  The one with Michael Keaton, Jack Nicholson, etc.  I really like it.  Michael Keaton does look rather intimidating as Batman but when he is out of costume he looks old.  It was kind of weird watching it after seeing Batman Begins.  By the way, is Fantastic Four any good?  My life has been pretty good.  I finished the final exam today for Music Tech.  It was a little too easy.  No class for the rest of the week.  I still have to work though.  I'm going home next Monday and will stay through Saturday.  I'm going to be living at the BCM this fall and spring.  That was determined a few weeks ago.  I can't say I'm going to like it.  I'll be in charge of maintaining the facilities, but the rent is $25 a month.  We don't have to pay for water or power.  Just rent and the phone bill.  Other than that my life is slow.  I can't wait until school starts back.  This summer went by fast, but that's fine with me.  Oh, I bought a snare drum stand for 25 dollars last Friday.  Wizard's Drum Shop isn't that great of a place, but he practically gave it to me.  There's my update.  You can also find me on myspace and xanga(bobwiley17).  Peace.

Well, if you have ever read a Batman comic book you realize that Batman Begins is really the only Batman movie that comes close to the comics.  Christian Bale is definitely the best guy to play Batman.  George Clooney-the funny but really unintimidating Batman, Val Kilmer-not really amazing, Michael Keaton-???, Christian Bale-well the easiest way to put it is that he was Batman.  He struck fear in the hearts of the criminals.  For all who think George Clooney was better read the comics.  Batman was never a "happy" guy.  He was very secretive.  Hands down, Batman Begins is the best Batman movie ever.(Michael Caine is also the best actor to play Alfred.)  On another note, don't go to see Dukes of Hazzard.  The only good thing is...you get the point.  Peace.

Well life as I know it may come to an end.(not really)  I was planning on going home(TN) to see my girlfriend, but now I found out I may not have enough money.  Stab me in the eye with a spoon.  So I'm either going to go and try to make it on a half tank of gas(which is extremely possible but risky in my car), or I'm going to stay here.  I'd rather go, but life always has a way of throwing curves and messing up your plans.  Well so long until tomorrow.

Star Wars Episode 3.  I think overall it was a great movie.  It did have some down time which was somewhat needed.  I was very pleased that George Lucas used James Earl Jones' voice for Darth Vader.  Had it been anybody but his I would have been very angry.  I didn't really like General Grievous' voice.  He breathed somewhat like Darth Vader, but not near as intimidating.  His continual coughing was annoying as well.  As far as the action scenes went I like them all.  I wish they would have shown more combat involving the wookies.  I wanted to see a wookie rip someone's arms out of their sockets.  I liked the movie, after all it wasn't as bad as The Phantom Menace.  I was pleased.

Has anyone seen Star Wars yet?  I turned down a ticket to go see it at midnight with my cousin.  I should have gone, but I would not have been able to wake up for my job at eight.  I'm going to see it sometime.  I've heard that it's better than any of the others.  I'll have to decide for myself.  I'm having fun being bored.  I actually practiced yesterday.  I'm such a loser.  The great thing about this week is that my girlfriend is at the beach and I'm not.  That stinks.  I'm tired of typing so I'm going to quit.

So I'm realy bored.  I love my job at computer services.  time is money.  After I work though, I'm bored.  Being on campus without people is scary.  I should be practicing after all I set up my drums yesterday.  This is really boring writing this.  I did go to a good wedding Saturday.  On top of being bored for the rest of the summer my girlfriend leaves this week to go to the beach.  I'm ready to shoot myself in the head.  Maybe.
